# No tar-ignore for target/ here on purpose. dpkg-source's --tar-ignore
# (used for "3.0 (native)" format instead of --diff-ignore, which only
# affects non-native diffs) matches path components anywhere in the tree,
# not just at the source root — a "target"-named pattern also strips
# vendor/cc/src/target/ (a real, needed subdirectory in the vendored `cc`
# crate), and a directory-name-scoped pattern like "linux-hello/target"
# only works if the working directory is literally named "linux-hello".
# Neither is reliable. Instead, debian/scripts/prepare-offline-build.sh
# removes target/ outright before packaging — see docs/LAUNCHPAD.md.
